A Hori-Hori, sometimes referred to as a "soil knife" or a "weeding knife", is a heavy serrated multi-purpose steel blade for gardening jobs such as digging or cutting. The blade is sharp on both sides and comes to a semi-sharp point at the end.  The word Hori means "to dig" in Japanese.  The tool itself is commonly referred to as a "leisure knife" or a "Sansai(=Mountain-vegetable) knife" in Japan. You remove the protective film from the adhesive side (this will be the side you actually place on your phone), then line up the glass above it (be care not to touch the adhesive side), and slowly lower it until it is resting on your screen. You can place your finger in the middle of the screen and you will be able to see it adhere to your phone. Smooth out any bubbles (I didn't have any), and that's it you're all done.
